reviews.text:
A restaurant located on 8/F at Life@KCC, a newly refurbished industrial building. I ate the lunch set "招牌咪走雞飯"(HKD68) , chicken without bones served in a pottery plate, with a plate of rice. 

I would say it is a bit overpriced, with the taste of too much seasonings(to me), and yet not too tasty for me. Snacks at tea time could be ordered at lunch time too in case you have to share snacks with your friends/ colleagues. But again, they are pricey in my opinion.

The place started to get crowded after 1230,so better grab your place before, otherwise you will have to queue and take ticket outside.

Dirty food (seen).

These paper mats kept dropping on the floor, staff kept picking them up and placing them back on the shelf (basically cause as you can see it's a very stupid place to place them there, workers hard to reach). For 30mins I've seen them drop for 3 times. I told one staff that they shouldn't be doing so, meh. The manager also dropped it, thought he'd be different but nope, stuffed 3 back in. You're basically eating off the floor, as they handle your food with those filthy hands as well. Food tastes OK though.
Quite pricey but food is ok for lunch
Signature chicken in soup, sweet and sour pork and minced pork rice all good.  Reasonably priced.
Set dinner for two or four is super value!

reviews.text: The ground floor has the best restaurants imo

A factory building converted into yet another food and retail complex filled mostly with typical chain stores. It comes from a very regretable government policy of "revitalising industrial buildings", which in effect allows property developers to change the land usage from industrial (buy low) to commerical (let out high) without a public tendering process.
Footbridge between KCC and MTR station. There are lot of restaurant in this building.
New shopping place.
唔算多地方行，细细地，不過感覺幾休閒，都算多野食

reviews.text: 厨師應該同生粉有仇，每一個菜的獻汁都係一劈劈，醬住d餸😂🤣收銀姨姨似乎只係喜歡收現金，俾卡會俾說話人聽。。。😅 下次唔敢去了。。。
經濟分量亦不細。唔係味噌湯好飲。小炒味道遍咸。雞個汁唔得。至於環境衛生不錯的。服務亦很好。但此店油煙味勁。第二次再去叫了同一款餐。湯依然好味冇味噌。但小炒冇味加勁難食由其個义燒炒蛋真係差到冇得再差。個雞韌到咬唔到。這水準真的不會再去。

晚飯抵食，服務親切

5人食4人餐($468+10%)  都差d食唔晒。包括招牌菜咪走雞半隻，西蘭花炒青衣柳，蝦球粉絲煲，再揀多兩個小菜，有例湯，白飯同甜品。

餸菜全部熱辣辣，咪走雞沙薑汁濃而不膩，砵底d椰菜同雲耳好清甜好味呀！ 

環境幾乾淨，星期六晚上都差唔多8成滿，好多一家人黎食。d姐姐服務好親切。甜品係熱辣辣蒸起薑汁糕，4人餐4件但送多件俾我地，一人一件，好滿足！

唔食小菜食番咪走雞飯/米線同花雕雞湯米線一樣得。

如果住葵芳，我覺得行10分鐘過黎食好過喺新都會食d 連鎖店，又多人又貴。讚！

A restaurant located on 8/F at Life@KCC, a newly refurbished industrial building. I ate the lunch set "招牌咪走雞飯"(HKD68) , chicken without bones served in a pottery plate, with a plate of rice. 

I would say it is a bit overpriced, with the taste of too much seasonings(to me), and yet not too tasty for me. Snacks at tea time could be ordered at lunch time too in case you have to share snacks with your friends/ colleagues. But again, they are pricey in my opinion.

The place started to get crowded after 1230,so better grab your place before, otherwise you will have to queue and take ticket outside.

地方闊落，坐得舒服，環境乾淨舒適，
必試花膠雞湯米粉，超足料，湯頭好飲味道夠！
